						               													<description>Eco-Marketing is an educational game in which kids and adults can learn what to do with their so called &amp;quot;rubbish&amp;quot;. Most of what we use at home can be reused to make new items, can be sold as recycling material, or even have more than one use. And just a few things are left to be thrown in the black plastic bag.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In your turn, you will be able to decide what to throw in the black plastic bag to get an Eco-point, sell recycling materials and collect money to enter the bet for the first player, and/or make new products, reusing things like plastic wraps, magazines, plastic bags, bottles, eggshells, inner-tires and bottles, that will give you not only points, but also bonuses to get new resources in your next turns.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     NOTE: Although instructions are in Spanish, the game can be played in any language, in any country, because cards, coins and board only have a few words, no long texts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
